host\n|type2-2=Poison\n|evo2={{bag|Pal Pad}}<br>{{color2|000|Trade}}\n|no3=094\n|name3=Gengar\n|type1-3=Ghost\n|type2-3=Poison}}\n\n===Sprites===\n{{Spritebox/Header|type=Ghost|type2=Poison}}\n{{Spritebox/1|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/2|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/3|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/4|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=093}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|093|Haunter}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* In the [[Pokémon Red and Green beta|Pokémon Red and Blue beta]], Haunter\'s prototype name was "Spectre".\n**The [[Pokémon Trainer\'s Survival Guide]] also erroneously references Haunter by this name on one page.\n* No other Pokémon have the same [[List of Pokémon with unique type combinations|type combination]] as Haunter and its evolutionary relatives.\n** Due to its unique type combination, Haunter and its evolutionary relatives are the only Poison-type Pokémon that are weak against Dark-type moves.\n* Haunter is the Pokémon with the most cry changes throughout the series, having been changed in generations [[Generation II|II]], [[Generation III|III]], and [[Generation VI|VI]].\n\n===Origin===\nHaunter appears to be based on a generic sort of cartoonish {{wp|ghost}}. Like Gengar, Haunter may also be based on the {{wp|Cheshire Cat}}, as it possesses what may be pointed ears; a large, toothy grin; and the ability to vanish at will.\n\n====Name origin====\nHaunter is derived from \'\'haunt\'\', as {{wp|ghost}}s are known to do. It could also be a corruption of "hunter".\n\nGhost is literally \'\'ghost\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ghost|type2=Poison\n|ja=ゴースト \'\'Ghost\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'ghost\'\'\n|fr=Spectrum|frmeaning=From \'\'spectre\'\'\n|es=Haunter|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Alpollo|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Alptraum|nightmare}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Apollo Program|Apollo}}\n|it=Haunter|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=고우스트 \'\'Goust\'\'|komeaning=Similar to Japanese name; from \'\'ghost\'\'\n|zh_yue=鬼斯通 \'\'Gwáisītūng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Rough transcription of its Japanese name. Also a combination of {{tt|鬼|ghost}}, {{tt|瓦斯|gas}}, and {{tt|通|to pass through}}.\n|zh_cmn=鬼斯通 \'\'Guǐsītōng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Rough transcription of its Japanese name. Also a combination of {{tt|鬼|ghost}}, {{tt|瓦斯|gas}}, and {{tt|通|to pass through}}.\n|he=הונטר \'\'Honter\'\'|hemeaning=Transcription of English name\n|hi=हौंटेर \'\'Haunter\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Хонтер \'\'Khonter\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{left clear}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Sabrina\'s Haunter]]\n* [[Black Fog]]\n<!--\n==Notes==\n<references />-->\n\n==External links==\n* {{wp|Haunter|Article on Wikipedia}}\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ghost|type2=Poison}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ghost|prevnum=092|prev=Gastly|nextnum=094|next=Gengar}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve through trading]]\n\n[[de:Alpollo]]\n[[es:Haunter]]\n[[fr:Spectrum]]\n[[it:Haunter]]\n[[ja:ゴースト]]\n[[zh:鬼斯通]]'}